WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.810 --> 00:00:05.707 align:middle line:84%
>> This is "Nuevo, the UFOs
of Los Alamos, New Mexico."

00:00:05.707 --> 00:00:08.569 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.569 --> 00:00:14.300 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:23.352 align:middle line:10%
>> Gaia presents "Nuevo"
with Jaime Maussan.

00:00:23.352 --> 00:00:29.150 align:middle line:90%


00:00:29.150 --> 00:00:32.930 align:middle line:10%
>> Traditional stories indicate
that the first extraterrestrial

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:37.640 align:middle line:10%
craft that we know crash landed
near Los Alamos in Roswell,

00:00:37.640 --> 00:00:41.420 align:middle line:10%
New Mexico on July 3rd, 1947.

00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:43.760 align:middle line:84%
However, recent
investigations have

00:00:43.760 --> 00:00:48.200 align:middle line:84%
shown that the first ship
fell just 18 miles from where

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:51.470 align:middle line:84%
the first atomic
bomb was detonated.

00:00:51.470 --> 00:00:54.620 align:middle line:84%
30 days after this
happened, the atomic bomb

00:00:54.620 --> 00:00:56.900 align:middle line:90%
was detonated on July 16th.

00:00:56.900 --> 00:01:01.680 align:middle line:84%
And on August 16th, precisely
in New Mexico in San Antonio,

00:01:01.680 --> 00:01:05.390 align:middle line:84%
this ship was seen to
crash land with up to four

00:01:05.390 --> 00:01:07.460 align:middle line:90%
extraterrestrials inside.

00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:09.070 align:middle line:90%
Quite a fantastic story.

00:01:09.070 --> 00:01:11.930 align:middle line:90%


00:01:11.930 --> 00:01:14.720 align:middle line:90%
>> San Antonio, New Mexico.

00:01:14.720 --> 00:01:19.940 align:middle line:84%
Almost two years before an alien
ship crash landed in Roswell,

00:01:19.940 --> 00:01:22.250 align:middle line:84%
a ship with four
occupants came down

00:01:22.250 --> 00:01:25.670 align:middle line:84%
just 18 miles from
that site, and 30 days

00:01:25.670 --> 00:01:29.300 align:middle line:84%
after the detonation of
the first atomic bomb test.

00:01:29.300 --> 00:01:34.400 align:middle line:10%
A memo from a special agent to
the director of the FBI in 1950

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:36.440 align:middle line:10%
discovered that there
were three ships that

00:01:36.440 --> 00:01:40.010 align:middle line:10%
crashed around the Los
Alamos nuclear power plant

00:01:40.010 --> 00:01:42.500 align:middle line:10%
in New Mexico.

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:45.680 align:middle line:84%
The documents said that
extraterrestrial beings had

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:48.650 align:middle line:84%
been recovered, and that the
ships had been brought down

00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:50.840 align:middle line:84%
as a result of the
powerful radars that

00:01:50.840 --> 00:01:54.220 align:middle line:90%
operated in the area.

00:01:54.220 --> 00:01:59.200 align:middle line:84%
On August 16, 1945, two
children 6 and 7 years old

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:02.590 align:middle line:84%
were looking for a cow in the
vicinity of a New Mexico ranch

00:02:02.590 --> 00:02:05.890 align:middle line:84%
just a few miles away
from the Trinity site.

00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:08.590 align:middle line:84%
These children witnessed
the crash landing

00:02:08.590 --> 00:02:12.160 align:middle line:84%
of an oval-shaped ship
that crashed into a tower

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:14.050 align:middle line:90%
and fell to the ground.

00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:17.320 align:middle line:84%
They saw beings with
nonhuman characteristics

00:02:17.320 --> 00:02:20.560 align:middle line:84%
who were barely larger
than themselves.

00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:23.080 align:middle line:84%
With binoculars, they
observed the little beings

00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:25.960 align:middle line:84%
for almost two
hours, an experience

00:02:25.960 --> 00:02:29.230 align:middle line:90%
that they would never forget.

00:02:29.230 --> 00:02:31.420 align:middle line:84%
Later, the army arrived,
and took the ship

00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:33.770 align:middle line:90%
to an unknown location.

00:02:33.770 --> 00:02:38.020 align:middle line:84%
However, the children, Jose
Padilla, and Reme Baca,

00:02:38.020 --> 00:02:41.830 align:middle line:84%
took a piece of metal from
inside the ship, a piece

00:02:41.830 --> 00:02:44.710 align:middle line:84%
that they have preserved
until this day.

00:02:44.710 --> 00:02:49.510 align:middle line:10%
Journalist Paola Harris was the
first to investigate this case,

00:02:49.510 --> 00:02:53.920 align:middle line:10%
and reached the conclusion
that it was authentic.

00:02:53.920 --> 00:02:57.340 align:middle line:10%
We had the opportunity to talk
with her at the historic Owl

00:02:57.340 --> 00:03:00.100 align:middle line:10%
Bar and Cafe, the
very same place

00:03:00.100 --> 00:03:02.770 align:middle line:10%
those people that participated
in the development

00:03:02.770 --> 00:03:07.370 align:middle line:10%
of the first atomic bomb met,
codenamed Manhattan Project.

00:03:07.370 --> 00:03:09.640 align:middle line:84%
They came to this
bar and cafe to talk

00:03:09.640 --> 00:03:12.836 align:middle line:84%
about these
extraordinary events.

00:03:12.836 --> 00:03:17.590 align:middle line:84%
>> So where did you find
the story of San Antonio?

00:03:17.590 --> 00:03:21.640 align:middle line:84%
Where did you find Jose
Padilla and Reme Baca?

00:03:21.640 --> 00:03:25.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, in about 2004,
I was living in Italy,

00:03:25.240 --> 00:03:30.670 align:middle line:84%
and I read a story by Ben
Moffett for the newspaper here

00:03:30.670 --> 00:03:32.290 align:middle line:90%
in San Antonio.

00:03:32.290 --> 00:03:34.170 align:middle line:90%
And I read this story--

00:03:34.170 --> 00:03:38.080 align:middle line:84%
it was on internet-- about two
little Mexican boys that had

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:40.500 align:middle line:90%
witnessed a crash with beings.

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:42.680 align:middle line:84%
And when I was in
Italy, I thought, well,

00:03:42.680 --> 00:03:44.980 align:middle line:84%
why isn't somebody
researching this?

00:03:44.980 --> 00:03:50.410 align:middle line:84%
Then years later, I got a tip
from a friend and the telephone

00:03:50.410 --> 00:03:51.670 align:middle line:90%
number of Reme Baca.

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:53.110 align:middle line:90%
He was one of those little boys.

00:03:53.110 --> 00:03:55.600 align:middle line:84%
I had already read the
Ben Moffett article.

00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:59.620 align:middle line:84%
And Ben Moffett went to
school with Reme and Jose,

00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:02.440 align:middle line:84%
so he knew about this story,
because they had told him.

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:06.530 align:middle line:84%
So I got a tip, and also
I got the telephone number

00:04:06.530 --> 00:04:09.950 align:middle line:84%
of Reme Baca, who lived
in Gig Harbor, Washington.

00:04:09.950 --> 00:04:13.300 align:middle line:90%
And I called for one solid year.

00:04:13.300 --> 00:04:17.420 align:middle line:10%
I called for one solid year
and made friends with him

00:04:17.420 --> 00:04:18.730 align:middle line:10%
so he would trust me.

00:04:18.730 --> 00:04:21.370 align:middle line:84%
And he began telling
me about this story.

00:04:21.370 --> 00:04:26.320 align:middle line:84%
Then he asked me to speak to
Jose, who was in California.

00:04:26.320 --> 00:04:27.670 align:middle line:90%
And I verified this story.

00:04:27.670 --> 00:04:30.640 align:middle line:84%
Because both men had
the very same story.

00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:34.360 align:middle line:84%
I wrote an article for X Times
in Italy about the story.

00:04:34.360 --> 00:04:35.700 align:middle line:90%
I contacted you.

00:04:35.700 --> 00:04:37.480 align:middle line:90%
I contacted James Fox.

00:04:37.480 --> 00:04:41.790 align:middle line:84%
I contacted Swiss TV,
who went to interview

00:04:41.790 --> 00:04:43.150 align:middle line:90%
Reme Baca in Washington.

00:04:43.150 --> 00:04:46.540 align:middle line:84%
Thank god I did that, because
like Don Schmitt says,

00:04:46.540 --> 00:04:48.010 align:middle line:90%
it's a race with the undertaker.

00:04:48.010 --> 00:04:51.010 align:middle line:84%
Because these people are
dying, and they are witnesses

00:04:51.010 --> 00:04:53.350 align:middle line:90%
to very amazing events.

00:04:53.350 --> 00:04:57.950 align:middle line:84%
So we have on camera, Reme
Baca, who died in June.

00:04:57.950 --> 00:05:02.200 align:middle line:84%
And today you have Jose Padilla,
who actually brought you

00:05:02.200 --> 00:05:03.340 align:middle line:90%
to the site.

00:05:03.340 --> 00:05:06.160 align:middle line:84%
And this is my job
as an investigator.

00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:09.180 align:middle line:84%
I've been working
at it since 2009.

00:05:09.180 --> 00:05:10.600 align:middle line:90%
We're at 2014.

00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:13.270 align:middle line:84%
Five years to work on
this story, which I think

00:05:13.270 --> 00:05:15.580 align:middle line:84%
is one of the most
amazing stories ever.

00:05:15.580 --> 00:05:19.630 align:middle line:84%
Because it connects to the
atomic bomb situation, which

00:05:19.630 --> 00:05:22.360 align:middle line:84%
I think was the
stimulus for a lot

00:05:22.360 --> 00:05:25.360 align:middle line:90%
of the crashes in New Mexico.

00:05:25.360 --> 00:05:29.650 align:middle line:84%
>> We are hearing about where
Robert Oppenheimer used to sit

00:05:29.650 --> 00:05:34.750 align:middle line:84%
and drink and relax and
talk about the bomb.

00:05:34.750 --> 00:05:36.120 align:middle line:90%
And nobody knew about it.

00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:37.235 align:middle line:90%
>> Nobody knew about it.

00:05:37.235 --> 00:05:39.650 align:middle line:84%
>> The bomb was detonated
not very far from here.

00:05:39.650 --> 00:05:41.590 align:middle line:90%
>> No, 18 miles from here.

00:05:41.590 --> 00:05:43.930 align:middle line:90%
And the crash site is behind us.

00:05:43.930 --> 00:05:47.380 align:middle line:84%
It's about maybe
seven or eight miles.

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And it's in the township
of San Antonio, New Mexico.

00:05:52.700 --> 00:05:58.780 align:middle line:84%
So all of these events took
place in August of 1945.

00:05:58.780 --> 00:06:00.130 align:middle line:90%
This bar is very important.

00:06:00.130 --> 00:06:04.757 align:middle line:84%
Because I really believe
that if there was a crash--

00:06:04.757 --> 00:06:06.340 align:middle line:84%
I mean, Oppenheimer
and the scientists

00:06:06.340 --> 00:06:08.058 align:middle line:90%
would have to know about it.

00:06:08.058 --> 00:06:09.850 align:middle line:84%
They would certainly
have to know about it.

00:06:09.850 --> 00:06:11.590 align:middle line:84%
And they may have
even gone on the site.

00:06:11.590 --> 00:06:12.670 align:middle line:90%
Because this was amazing.

00:06:12.670 --> 00:06:14.320 align:middle line:90%
This was news.

00:06:14.320 --> 00:06:16.600 align:middle line:84%
This was something
that affected them.

00:06:16.600 --> 00:06:19.420 align:middle line:10%
So I think that in those
days, the scientists that

00:06:19.420 --> 00:06:22.570 align:middle line:10%
were working on this knew very
well that there were crashes,

00:06:22.570 --> 00:06:27.280 align:middle line:10%
and they were related to either
the high intensity radar that

00:06:27.280 --> 00:06:30.922 align:middle line:10%
brought them down, or some
kind of environmental thing

00:06:30.922 --> 00:06:31.880 align:middle line:10%
that brought them down.

00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:36.700 align:middle line:84%
But the visitations in those
days was around this big event.

00:06:36.700 --> 00:06:40.780 align:middle line:84%
This planet had discovered
the nuclear age.

00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:43.606 align:middle line:90%


00:06:43.606 --> 00:06:49.370 align:middle line:84%
>> And the crash, according to
how it was reported it happened

00:06:49.370 --> 00:06:53.560 align:middle line:84%
when I was 16, just a month
after the atomic bomb was

00:06:53.560 --> 00:06:54.360 align:middle line:90%
detonated.

00:06:54.360 --> 00:06:55.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:06:55.750 --> 00:06:57.920 align:middle line:84%
But there are photographs--
and I have some--

00:06:57.920 --> 00:07:02.280 align:middle line:84%
of the men on the Trinity
site with the mushroom

00:07:02.280 --> 00:07:04.650 align:middle line:84%
cloud with UFOs
in the background.

00:07:04.650 --> 00:07:06.390 align:middle line:90%
They have been leaked out.

00:07:06.390 --> 00:07:11.340 align:middle line:84%
So when we did that, it upset
something in the environment,

00:07:11.340 --> 00:07:15.740 align:middle line:84%
or in dimensions, where
it caused this phenomenon.

00:07:15.740 --> 00:07:18.300 align:middle line:84%
And you know that it's
the birth of ufology.

00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:21.150 align:middle line:84%
Roswell is considered
mythologically, the birth

00:07:21.150 --> 00:07:23.310 align:middle line:90%
of the modern UFO era.

00:07:23.310 --> 00:07:25.840 align:middle line:84%
But this is even more
amazing, because it's 1945,

00:07:25.840 --> 00:07:28.716 align:middle line:90%
which is two years before.

00:07:28.716 --> 00:07:32.850 align:middle line:10%
>> Thus the case of the San
Antonio alien incident would

00:07:32.850 --> 00:07:37.770 align:middle line:10%
join the cases that occurred in
Roswell and Aztec, New Mexico.

00:07:37.770 --> 00:07:40.440 align:middle line:84%
