they had a clear vision of
the beings that were injured

00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:39.120 align:middle line:90%
in the ship.

00:11:39.120 --> 00:11:43.320 align:middle line:84%
They all appeared hurt, and one
of them couldn't move at all.

00:11:43.320 --> 00:11:45.450 align:middle line:84%
The children watched
them with binoculars

00:11:45.450 --> 00:11:48.216 align:middle line:90%
for almost two hours.

00:11:48.216 --> 00:11:49.995 align:middle line:90%
>> But it was--

00:11:49.995 --> 00:11:51.960 align:middle line:90%
>> You saw the little creatures?

00:11:51.960 --> 00:11:54.690 align:middle line:84%
>> From here, yes,
with the binoculars.

00:11:54.690 --> 00:11:55.490 align:middle line:90%
We used--

00:11:55.490 --> 00:11:55.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you had binoculars?

00:11:55.650 --> 00:11:56.360 align:middle line:90%
>> --to carry binoculars.

00:11:56.360 --> 00:11:57.960 align:middle line:84%
Oh yeah, we had
carried binoculars.

00:11:57.960 --> 00:12:00.574 align:middle line:90%
I still have them.

00:12:00.574 --> 00:12:02.990 align:middle line:84%
>> That's why you
saw them so clearly?

00:12:02.990 --> 00:12:04.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah!

00:12:04.400 --> 00:12:07.845 align:middle line:90%
>> Both of you.

00:12:07.845 --> 00:12:10.090 align:middle line:90%
How many creatures you saw?

00:12:10.090 --> 00:12:10.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Four.

00:12:10.890 --> 00:12:12.246 align:middle line:90%
>> Four creatures?

00:12:12.246 --> 00:12:15.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Four.

00:12:15.410 --> 00:12:19.040 align:middle line:90%
Three of them were running--

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:21.110 align:middle line:84%
you could see it
through that hole--

00:12:21.110 --> 00:12:28.000 align:middle line:84%
running back and forth like they
were hurt, they were injured.

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:32.140 align:middle line:84%
And the other one just sitting
right there in the side.

00:12:32.140 --> 00:12:36.280 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if that
guy was dead or was hurt

00:12:36.280 --> 00:12:38.260 align:middle line:90%
and couldn't move.

00:12:38.260 --> 00:12:43.040 align:middle line:84%
That's why I decided to
go down there to help him.

00:12:43.040 --> 00:12:47.140 align:middle line:90%
But Reme doesn't let me.

00:12:47.140 --> 00:12:48.400 align:middle line:90%
He was scared.

00:12:48.400 --> 00:12:51.310 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, I told
you before, maybe

00:12:51.310 --> 00:12:54.220 align:middle line:84%
if I would have gone up there,
I wouldn't be here today,

00:12:54.220 --> 00:12:55.510 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:12:55.510 --> 00:12:59.020 align:middle line:90%
I'd be somewhere else, you know?

00:12:59.020 --> 00:13:01.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Were they screaming?

00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:05.280 align:middle line:84%
>> They had a scream
like a jackrabbit.

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:07.920 align:middle line:84%
What do you call a
jackrabbit in Spanish?

00:13:07.920 --> 00:13:08.720 align:middle line:90%
La liebre?

00:13:08.720 --> 00:13:09.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Si.

00:13:09.520 --> 00:13:11.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Liebre.

00:13:11.050 --> 00:13:13.380 align:middle line:84%
Like, when we used to
shoot them and they

00:13:13.380 --> 00:13:17.350 align:middle line:84%
used to squeal
[SQUEALING] like a baby.

00:13:17.350 --> 00:13:22.005 align:middle line:84%
That's why I say that they
were hurt, they were injured.

00:13:22.005 --> 00:13:24.981 align:middle line:90%
>> All of them were screaming?

00:13:24.981 --> 00:13:26.120 align:middle line:90%
>> All?

00:13:26.120 --> 00:13:27.120 align:middle line:90%
we don't know, you know?

00:13:27.120 --> 00:13:30.670 align:middle line:84%
It was off and on,
off and on, you know?

00:13:30.670 --> 00:13:35.580 align:middle line:84%
But we were here for
about an hour and a half,

00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:39.150 align:middle line:84%
almost an hour and 45 minutes,
two hours watching them.

00:13:39.150 --> 00:13:42.516 align:middle line:84%
>> You saw them
very, very clear?

00:13:42.516 --> 00:13:44.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh yeah.

00:13:44.070 --> 00:13:49.110 align:middle line:84%
They were-- like I said, I
could see the four fingers,

00:13:49.110 --> 00:13:52.200 align:middle line:90%
the long arms.

00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:56.190 align:middle line:90%
And they didn't have no ears.

00:13:56.190 --> 00:14:02.380 align:middle line:84%
So I thought maybe they had
an overall or a uniform.

00:14:02.380 --> 00:14:11.760 align:middle line:90%
But the mouth was kind of small.

00:14:11.760 --> 00:14:14.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's what the
song was coming out of.

00:14:14.670 --> 00:14:18.990 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't a mouth
like ours, you know?

00:14:18.990 --> 00:14:24.075 align:middle line:84%
No beard, it was just a
straight slicker like a uniform.

00:14:24.075 --> 00:14:27.216 align:middle line:90%


00:14:27.216 --> 00:14:30.850 align:middle line:84%
>> What kind of
insect remind you?

00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:37.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Like hormiga, an ant--
you know those red ants?--

00:14:37.290 --> 00:14:39.130 align:middle line:90%
standing up.

00:14:39.130 --> 00:14:42.068 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever seen
them standing up?

00:14:42.068 --> 00:14:43.110 align:middle line:90%
It's something like that.

00:14:43.110 --> 00:14:47.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Somebody said in Spanish,
it would be cara de niño.

00:14:47.510 --> 00:14:49.030 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:14:49.030 --> 00:14:51.190 align:middle line:84%
>> There is another
red thing like--

00:14:51.190 --> 00:14:51.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Maybe--

00:14:51.990 --> 00:14:53.490 align:middle line:90%
>> --niño de la tierra.

00:14:53.490 --> 00:14:54.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Si.

00:14:54.530 --> 00:14:56.130 align:middle line:90%
>> It's something like that.

00:14:56.130 --> 00:15:00.580 align:middle line:90%
It almost resembles an ant.

00:15:00.580 --> 00:15:06.060 align:middle line:84%
But if you would get
an ant and draw it up--

00:15:06.060 --> 00:15:07.690 align:middle line:90%
a big picture of it--

00:15:07.690 --> 00:15:11.210 align:middle line:84%
it would be something like
that except for the arms.

00:15:11.210 --> 00:15:13.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Children of the earth?

00:15:13.350 --> 00:15:17.390 align:middle line:90%
>> Children on the Earth, yeah.

00:15:17.390 --> 00:15:19.160 align:middle line:90%
There was something like that.

00:15:19.160 --> 00:15:23.655 align:middle line:84%
But the niño de la
tierra is usually curled.

00:15:23.655 --> 00:15:26.270 align:middle line:90%


00:15:26.270 --> 00:15:28.960 align:middle line:84%
Now if he was
straightened upright,

00:15:28.960 --> 00:15:32.110 align:middle line:84%
he would resemble
something like that.

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:33.950 align:middle line:90%
And according to the head--

00:15:33.950 --> 00:15:38.580 align:middle line:84%
the head more likely
look like an ant.

00:15:38.580 --> 00:15:46.164 align:middle line:84%
It was shaped like that, with
teardrop eyes and no ears.

00:15:46.164 --> 00:15:47.902 align:middle line:90%
>> How tall?

00:15:47.902 --> 00:15:52.390 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, we were about that tall.

00:15:52.390 --> 00:15:54.450 align:middle line:90%
I would say 3 and 1/2 feet.

00:15:54.450 --> 00:15:57.770 align:middle line:90%


00:15:57.770 --> 00:15:58.590 align:middle line:90%
>> 3 and 1/2 feet?

00:15:58.590 --> 00:15:59.790 align:middle line:90%
>> About 3 and 1/2 feet.

00:15:59.790 --> 00:16:00.590 align:middle line:90%
Just like us.

00:16:00.590 --> 00:16:04.160 align:middle line:84%
You know, we were little
kids then, you know?

00:16:04.160 --> 00:16:06.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Did you feel scared by them?

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:07.300 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:16:07.300 --> 00:16:08.100 align:middle line:90%
>> No?

00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>> No, I have never
been scared of nothing.

00:16:11.300 --> 00:16:14.545 align:middle line:84%
That's why I wanted to
go in there, you know?

00:16:14.545 --> 00:16:16.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Were you impressed?

00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:19.210 align:middle line:84%
Did you know they weren't
from the earth at that moment?

00:16:19.210 --> 00:16:20.350 align:middle line:90%
>> No?

00:16:20.350 --> 00:16:21.267 align:middle line:90%
>> What did you think?

00:16:21.267 --> 00:16:24.760 align:middle line:84%
>> I thought that
something crashed,

00:16:24.760 --> 00:16:26.760 align:middle line:84%
that those guys
out there are hurt.

00:16:26.760 --> 00:16:29.590 align:middle line:90%
Let's go help them, you know.

00:16:29.590 --> 00:16:33.130 align:middle line:84%
My intentions has been
for life, you know?

00:16:33.130 --> 00:16:38.170 align:middle line:84%
If I see anybody getting hurt,
I try to go and help them

00:16:38.170 --> 00:16:39.330 align:middle line:90%
if I can help.

00:16:39.330 --> 00:16:41.530 align:middle line:84%
If I can't help, I
just go around and keep

00:16:41.530 --> 00:16:43.090 align:middle line:90%
on going my way, you know?

00:16:43.090 --> 00:16:44.980 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I
thought about this.

00:16:44.980 --> 00:16:47.230 align:middle line:84%
They were running back and
forth, squealing, you know?

00:16:47.230 --> 00:16:50.298 align:middle line:84%
>> Did you realize
they were not humans?

00:16:50.298 --> 00:16:55.210 align:middle line:84%
>> To me, they looked like
little boys since they were

00:16:55.210 --> 00:16:56.890 align:middle line:90%
short, you know?

00:16:56.890 --> 00:16:59.740 align:middle line:84%
The only thing different
on them that was surprising

00:16:59.740 --> 00:17:02.590 align:middle line:84%
is the four fingers
and the long arms.

00:17:02.590 --> 00:17:06.640 align:middle line:84%
Then I remember a monkey
has got long arms.

00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:09.730 align:middle line:84%
>> When did you realize that
what you saw probably was not

00:17:09.730 --> 00:17:10.530 align:middle line:90%
from this earth?

00:17:10.530 --> 00:17:14.440 align:middle line:90%


00:17:14.440 --> 00:17:19.240 align:middle line:84%
>> I never thought anything
about that until they started

00:17:19.240 --> 00:17:25.089 align:middle line:84%
bringing out that UFOs,
like Roswell and all that.

00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:30.200 align:middle line:84%
That's when I thought, well,
was that thing that we've seen,

00:17:30.200 --> 00:17:32.560 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:17:32.560 --> 00:17:35.470 align:middle line:84%
>> It is remarkable the
similarity of the description

00:17:35.470 --> 00:17:38.980 align:middle line:84%
that was offered by witnesses
who observed what appeared

00:17:38.980 --> 00:17:43.720 align:middle line:84%
to be alien beings in the
cases of Roswell and Aztec,

00:17:43.720 --> 00:17:48.670 align:middle line:84%
and what also occurred in New
Mexico in subsequent years.

00:17:48.670 --> 00:17:51.700 align:middle line:84%
Four days after the
accident on August 20th,

00:17:51.700 --> 00:17:53.800 align:middle line:84%
seven members of the
army were assigned

00:17:53.800 --> 00:17:57.910 align:middle line:84%
to the security of the
Los Alamos nuclear base,

00:17:57.910 --> 00:18:01.600 align:middle line:84%
the same men that had
participated as test subjects

00:18:01.600 --> 00:18:06.016 align:middle line:84%
to measure the effects of
the atomic bomb on humans.

00:18:06.016 --> 00:18:10.766 align:middle line:84%
>> Who told the military
that this craft was here?

00:18:10.766 --> 00:18:18.040 align:middle line:84%
>> That William Bodi
from Hollywood, Florida,

00:18:18.040 --> 00:18:23.000 align:middle line:84%
was assigned from the Stallion
site in White Sands on a plane

00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:26.530 align:middle line:84%
to check around for
weather balloons.

00:18:26.530 --> 00:18:30.200 align:middle line:10%
And that's when he
reported that there

00:18:30.200 --> 00:18:35.210 align:middle line:10%
was an object on the ground,
and there was two little Indians

00:18:35.210 --> 00:18:37.070 align:middle line:10%
on horses watching it.

00:18:37.070 --> 00:18:39.695 align:middle line:90%
That's what we were here.

00:18:39.695 --> 00:18:40.700 align:middle line:90%
>> He saw you?

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:42.868 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, he saw us.

00:18:42.868 --> 00:18:43.910 align:middle line:90%
He reported us, you know?

00:18:43.910 --> 00:18:49.550 align:middle line:84%
We were two little
Indians on two horses.

00:18:49.550 --> 00:18:51.518 align:middle line:84%
And that's when they
started coming in

00:18:51.518 --> 00:18:56.886 align:middle line:84%
after-- this was about four
days after it had happened.

00:18:56.886 --> 00:19:02.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Jose and Remigio watched the
military work for several days.

00:19:02.520 --> 00:19:05.120 align:middle line:84%
They were waiting for a
chance to grab a souvenir

00:19:05.120 --> 00:19:09.470 align:middle line:84%
from the ship to remember
their experience.

00:19:09.470 --> 00:19:12.440 align:middle line:84%
They didn't know that it
was a ship from outer space

00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:15.980 align:middle line:90%
that held nonhuman beings.

00:19:15.980 --> 00:19:19.370 align:middle line:84%
In 1945, that concept
did not exist, especially

00:19:19.370 --> 00:19:21.710 align:middle line:84%
for two children who
were born and raised

00:19:21.710 --> 00:19:26.520 align:middle line:84%
in the countryside
far from civilization.

00:19:26.520 --> 00:19:30.330 align:middle line:84%
They just wanted
a little souvenir.

00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:33.870 align:middle line:84%
After the soldiers loaded
the ship onto a truck,

00:19:33.870 --> 00:19:37.860 align:middle line:84%
they drove it to an old
barn in San Antonio.

00:19:37.860 --> 00:19:40.620 align:middle line:84%
It was there that
they entered the ship

00:19:40.620 --> 00:19:42.720 align:middle line:84%
and took a souvenir,
which they have

00:19:42.720 --> 00:19:48.984 align:middle line:84%
kept for more than 70 years
and are now revealing to us.

00:19:48.984 --> 00:19:52.290 align:middle line:84%
>> The last day that they
came over and they loaded up

00:19:52.290 --> 00:19:55.770 align:middle line:84%
everything up here, put
the tarp on it, the ropes.

00:19:55.770 --> 00:19:59.250 align:middle line:84%
We were hiding up
there looking at them.

00:19:59.250 --> 00:20:03.570 align:middle line:84%
All seven of them all got
in the Jeep in the evening

00:20:03.570 --> 00:20:06.620 align:middle line:84%
and took off to go see
the girls in the Owl Bar.

00:20:06.620 --> 00:20:08.576 align:middle line:90%
>> And that's up there?

00:20:08.576 --> 00:20:11.700 align:middle line:84%
>> That's when we decided
to come down here.

00:20:11.700 --> 00:20:14.562 align:middle line:90%
There was no one over here.

00:20:14.562 --> 00:20:17.580 align:middle line:84%
>> The craft was in
the trailer already?

00:20:17.580 --> 00:20:21.880 align:middle line:84%
>> It was on the trailer with a
tarp on top and the ropes tied

00:20:21.880 --> 00:20:22.680 align:middle line:90%
down.

00:20:22.680 --> 00:20:24.190 align:middle line:90%
>> And was alone here?

00:20:24.190 --> 00:20:25.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, by itself, yeah.

00:20:25.600 --> 00:20:26.400 align:middle line:90%
There was no one.

00:20:26.400 --> 00:20:30.050 align:middle line:84%
They took off on the Jeep
and took off, you know?

00:20:30.050 --> 00:20:33.700 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what
time they came back,

00:20:33.700 --> 00:20:39.120 align:middle line:84%
but that object was moved
that night around 12 o'clock.

00:20:39.120 --> 00:20:42.855 align:middle line:84%
Because at 12 o'clock,
San Antonio is asleep.

00:20:42.855 --> 00:20:46.470 align:middle line:90%


00:20:46.470 --> 00:20:51.150 align:middle line:84%
And the following day, we came
out here and it wasn't here.

00:20:51.150 --> 00:20:54.818 align:middle line:84%
But we had seen
it the day before.

00:20:54.818 --> 00:20:59.000 align:middle line:84%
>> It wasn't long before the
military realized that a piece

00:20:59.000 --> 00:21:02.726 align:middle line:84%
from the inside of
the ship was missing.

00:21:02.726 --> 00:21:06.080 align:middle line:84%
>> They took inventory of what
they loaded on the trailer.

00:21:06.080 --> 00:21:08.620 align:middle line:90%


00:21:08.620 --> 00:21:11.560 align:middle line:84%
But like I said, someone broke
in there and took something.

00:21:11.560 --> 00:21:13.720 align:middle line:84%
When they got over there,
they took inventory,

00:21:13.720 --> 00:21:15.530 align:middle line:90%
and a piece was missing.

00:21:15.530 --> 00:21:18.550 align:middle line:90%


00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:19.995 align:middle line:84%
They couldn't find
out who it was.

00:21:19.995 --> 00:21:21.240 align:middle line:90%
>> They came back?

00:21:21.240 --> 00:21:27.380 align:middle line:84%
>> They came back two days
afterwards to my dad's ranch,

00:21:27.380 --> 00:21:32.280 align:middle line:84%
the house, and asked, seeing
if there was anything that

00:21:32.280 --> 00:21:34.590 align:middle line:90%
belonged to the military.

00:21:34.590 --> 00:21:36.700 align:middle line:84%
That's when my dad
told Manuel, there's

00:21:36.700 --> 00:21:41.680 align:middle line:84%
some weather balloons that are
sitting out there on the shack,

00:21:41.680 --> 00:21:42.870 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:21:42.870 --> 00:21:44.620 align:middle line:84%
They went over and
they took that.

00:21:44.620 --> 00:21:53.160 align:middle line:84%
But afterwards-- back
in 1965, my cousin

00:21:53.160 --> 00:21:57.270 align:middle line:84%
was driving up here to
go check the windmill.

00:21:57.270 --> 00:22:01.500 align:middle line:84%
And they pulled him over
before the cattle guard.

00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:06.410 align:middle line:84%
The soldiers pulled him over
and they wouldn't let him cross.

00:22:06.410 --> 00:22:07.210 align:middle line:90%
>> Why?

00:22:07.210 --> 00:22:10.300 align:middle line:84%
>> They went after
something that was missing.

00:22:10.300 --> 00:22:12.270 align:middle line:90%
>> They didn't come here?

00:22:12.270 --> 00:22:15.215 align:middle line:84%
>> It possible that
they were out here too.

00:22:15.215 --> 00:22:17.090 align:middle line:84%
But they were stopping
all traffic out there.

00:22:17.090 --> 00:22:20.060 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a Y where you
go to Biancas and Padilla.

00:22:20.060 --> 00:22:25.070 align:middle line:84%
>> So you think they came to
look for the pieces here or no?

00:22:25.070 --> 00:22:27.610 align:middle line:90%


00:22:27.610 --> 00:22:30.250 align:middle line:90%
>> It's possible that they did.

00:22:30.250 --> 00:22:32.910 align:middle line:84%
But they didn't look
too good, though.

00:22:32.910 --> 00:22:36.950 align:middle line:84%
>> According to Jose Padilla,
some of the parts of the ship

00:22:36.950 --> 00:22:39.941 align:middle line:90%
are still buried at the site.

00:22:39.941 --> 00:22:42.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Where did they bury
the pieces, right there,

00:22:42.290 --> 00:22:43.690 align:middle line:90%
right here?

00:22:43.690 --> 00:22:45.990 align:middle line:84%
>> No, the crevice
was right here.

00:22:45.990 --> 00:22:49.182 align:middle line:90%


00:22:49.182 --> 00:22:50.250 align:middle line:90%
It was right here.

00:22:50.250 --> 00:22:52.330 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] sitting right
there, and the crevice

00:22:52.330 --> 00:22:53.810 align:middle line:90%
was right next to it.

00:22:53.810 --> 00:22:57.390 align:middle line:84%
And they used to come
down and come right-- see

00:22:57.390 --> 00:22:59.670 align:middle line:90%
where that clay is right there?

00:22:59.670 --> 00:23:02.732 align:middle line:84%
Used to come right
straight down like that.

00:23:02.732 --> 00:23:03.825 align:middle line:90%
>> The stream?

00:23:03.825 --> 00:23:05.230 align:middle line:90%
>> The stream, yeah.

00:23:05.230 --> 00:23:06.382 align:middle line:90%
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

