out of operation in 1957,

00:29:31.150 --> 00:29:35.530 align:middle line:84%
because they were very dangerous
for aircraft and for humans.

00:29:35.530 --> 00:29:38.530 align:middle line:10%
We do know that very powerful
experimental models were

00:29:38.530 --> 00:29:44.990 align:middle line:10%
used that transmitted microwaves
and emitted ionized radiation.

00:29:44.990 --> 00:29:48.580 align:middle line:84%
There are no studies
of how many people died

00:29:48.580 --> 00:29:52.450 align:middle line:84%
and how many planes were
lost with that technology

00:29:52.450 --> 00:29:57.390 align:middle line:84%
between 1945 and
1959 in New Mexico.

00:29:57.390 --> 00:30:00.400 align:middle line:84%
However, there was a study
conducted in Belgium,

00:30:00.400 --> 00:30:03.070 align:middle line:90%
which was recently published.

00:30:03.070 --> 00:30:05.430 align:middle line:10%
And according to their
findings, the exposure

00:30:05.430 --> 00:30:07.350 align:middle line:10%
of professional
military personnel

00:30:07.350 --> 00:30:12.360 align:middle line:10%
to antiaircraft radars used
in Europe in the '50s and '60s

00:30:12.360 --> 00:30:16.140 align:middle line:10%
